ciscoServiceControlTpStatsMIB.name: ciscoServiceControlTpStatsMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

ciscoServiceControlTpStatsMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-excelsior-dev@cisco.com
ciscoServiceControlTpStatsMIB.description: This MIB provides information and statistics on the traffic processor(s) of a service control entity, which is a network element that monitors network traffic between network subscribers based on user configured policies. A service control entity uses traffic processor(s) for packet processing and flow handling in the host network. The traffic processor(s) data obtained from this MIB may also reflect the general load in the system.

cscTpTable.name: cscTpTable
cscTpTable.description: This table contains the traffic processor statistics.

cscTpEntry.name: cscTpEntry
cscTpEntry.description: This entry lists traffic data for packets and flows handled by the traffic processor, identified by the entPhysicalIndex for an entity with its entPhysicalClass equal to 'cpu' in ENTITY-MIB.

cscTpTotalHandledPackets.name: cscTpTotalHandledPackets
cscTpTotalHandledPackets.description: This object indicates the number of packets handled by this traffic processor since last restart. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of cscTpCounterDiscontinuityTime.

cscTpTotalHandledFlows.name: cscTpTotalHandledFlows
cscTpTotalHandledFlows.description: This object indicates the number of flows handled by this traffic processor since last restart. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of cscTpCounterDiscontinuityTime.

cscTpActiveFlows.name: cscTpActiveFlows
cscTpActiveFlows.description: This object indicates the number of flows currently being handled by this traffic processor.

cscTpTcpActiveFlows.name: cscTpTcpActiveFlows
cscTpTcpActiveFlows.description: This object indicates the number of TCP flows currently being handled by this traffic processor.

cscTpUdpActiveFlows.name: cscTpUdpActiveFlows
cscTpUdpActiveFlows.description: This object indicates the number of UDP flows currently being handled by this traffic processor.

cscTpTotalBlockedPackets.name: cscTpTotalBlockedPackets
cscTpTotalBlockedPackets.description: This object indicates the number of packets discarded by this traffic processor due to application blocking rules. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of cscTpCounterDiscontinuityTime.

cscTpTotalBlockedFlows.name: cscTpTotalBlockedFlows
cscTpTotalBlockedFlows.description: This object indicates the number of flows discarded by this traffic processor due to application blocking rules. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of cscTpCounterDiscontinuityTime.

cscTpTotalBandwidthDiscardedPackets.name: cscTpTotalBandwidthDiscardedPackets
cscTpTotalBandwidthDiscardedPackets.description: This object indicates the number of packets discarded by this traffic processor due to subscriber bandwidth limitations. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of cscTpCounterDiscontinuityTime.

cscTpTotalWredDiscardedPackets.name: cscTpTotalWredDiscardedPackets
cscTpTotalWredDiscardedPackets.description: This object indicates the number of packets discarded by this traffic processor due to congestion in the queues. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of cscTpCounterDiscontinuityTime.

cscTpTotalFragments.name: cscTpTotalFragments
cscTpTotalFragments.description: This object indicates the number of fragmented packets handled by this traffic processor. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of cscTpCounterDiscontinuityTime.

cscTpTotalNonIpPackets.name: cscTpTotalNonIpPackets
cscTpTotalNonIpPackets.description: This object indicates the number of non IP packets handled by this traffic processor. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of cscTpCounterDiscontinuityTime.

cscTpTotalIpChecksumErrPackets.name: cscTpTotalIpChecksumErrPackets
cscTpTotalIpChecksumErrPackets.description: This object indicates the number of packets with IP checksum error handled by this traffic processor. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of cscTpCounterDiscontinuityTime.

cscTpTotalIpLengthErrPackets.name: cscTpTotalIpLengthErrPackets
cscTpTotalIpLengthErrPackets.description: This object indicates the number of packets with IP length error handled by this traffic processor. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of cscTpCounterDiscontinuityTime.

cscTpTotalIpBroadcastPackets.name: cscTpTotalIpBroadcastPackets
cscTpTotalIpBroadcastPackets.description: This object indicates the number of IP broadcast packets handled by this traffic processor. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of cscTpCounterDiscontinuityTime.

cscTpTotalTTLErrPackets.name: cscTpTotalTTLErrPackets
cscTpTotalTTLErrPackets.description: This object indicates the number of packets with TTL error handled by this traffic processor. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of cscTpCounterDiscontinuityTime.

cscTpTotalTcpUdpChksumErrPackets.name: cscTpTotalTcpUdpChksumErrPackets
cscTpTotalTcpUdpChksumErrPackets.description: This object indicates the number of TCP/UDP packets with checksum error handled by this traffic processor. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of cscTpCounterDiscontinuityTime.

cscTpHandledPacketsRate.name: cscTpHandledPacketsRate
cscTpHandledPacketsRate.description: This object indicates the number of packets handled by this traffic processor per second.

cscTpHandledFlowsRate.name: cscTpHandledFlowsRate
cscTpHandledFlowsRate.description: This object indicates the number of flow initiations per second on this traffic processor.

cscTpFlowsCapacityUtilization.name: cscTpFlowsCapacityUtilization
cscTpFlowsCapacityUtilization.description: This object indicates the percentage of open flows on this traffic processor out of the maximum supported number of flows per traffic processor.

cscTpServiceLoss.name: cscTpServiceLoss
cscTpServiceLoss.description: This object indicates the relative amount of service loss in this traffic processor, in units of 0.001%, since last restart.

cscTpStatsTrafficCountersTable.name: cscTpStatsTrafficCountersTable
cscTpStatsTrafficCountersTable.description: This table contains various traffic counters pertaining to traffic processing by the service control entity. These counters are defined, maintained and uniquely named by the service control entity hosted by traffic processor(s) at run time.

cscTpStatsTrafficCountersEntry.name: cscTpStatsTrafficCountersEntry
cscTpStatsTrafficCountersEntry.description: This entry contains the traffic counter data for a specific traffic counter defined by the service control entity at run time. The service control entity is indicated by entPhysicalIndex in the ENTITY-MIB with entPhysicalClass of either 'module' or 'chassis'.

cscTpStatsTrafficCounterIndex.name: cscTpStatsTrafficCounterIndex
cscTpStatsTrafficCounterIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies the counter.

cscTpStatsTrafficCounterName.name: cscTpStatsTrafficCounterName
cscTpStatsTrafficCounterName.description: This object indicates the human-readable name of this counter. The name is assigned by the service control entity when this counter is created at run time.

cscTpStatsTrafficCounterValue.name: cscTpStatsTrafficCounterValue
cscTpStatsTrafficCounterValue.description: This object indicates a 64 bit counter value. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of cscTpCounterDiscontinuityTime.

cscTpStatsTrafficCounterType.name: cscTpStatsTrafficCounterType
cscTpStatsTrafficCounterType.description: Specifies the measurement unit of the traffic counters measured by cscTpStatsTrafficCounterValue and described by cscTpStatsTrafficCounterName. 'packets' : counts by packets 'bytes' : counts by bytes 'other' : none of the above.

cscTpCounterDiscontinuityTime.name: cscTpCounterDiscontinuityTime
cscTpCounterDiscontinuityTime.description: The value of sysUpTime on the most recent occasion at which any one or more of the traffic processors's counters suffered a discontinuity. If no such discontinuities have occurred since the last re-initialization of the local management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

cscTpStatsMIBCompliance.name: cscTpStatsMIBCompliance
cscTpStatsMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for SNMP Agents which implement this MIB.

cscTpStatsMIBObjectGroup.name: cscTpStatsMIBObjectGroup
cscTpStatsMIBObjectGroup.description: This group is a collection of objects for traffic processor counters related to handling data.

cscTpStatsMIBTrafficCntrsObjGroup.name: cscTpStatsMIBTrafficCntrsObjGroup
cscTpStatsMIBTrafficCntrsObjGroup.description: This group is a collection of objects for general traffic processor counters.

cscTpCounterDiscontinuityGroup.name: cscTpCounterDiscontinuityGroup
cscTpCounterDiscontinuityGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information specific to traffic processor counter discontinuities.
